BUG-78FFAD05	bug_78ffad05	Postgres authority failures are flattened before the caller sees the real bootstrap context	FIXED	P3	P3	Observability gap: `storage/postgres/connection.py` normalizes pool/connect/bootstrap failures into `postgres.authority_unavailable`, and `surfaces/mcp/protocol.py` further flattens `PermissionError` 	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 12:34:43.587904-07	2026-04-16 13:55:44.795757-07	2026-04-16 12:34:43.587904-07	2026-04-16 13:55:44.795757-07	VERIFY	Observability gap: `storage/postgres/connection.py` normalizes pool/connect/bootstrap failures into `postgres.authority_unavailable`, and `surfaces/mcp/protocol.py` further flattens `PermissionError` to a bare string. That strips the authority target, DSN, and failing bootstrap step from the caller-visible error, so operators can chase the wrong layer when the real problem is in startup wiring or connection bootstrap. Evidence: `create_workflow_pool()`, `connect_workflow_database()`, `ensure_postgres_available()`, and `_format_tool_error()`. Next step: preserve the underlying exception type and the resolved authority in structured error payloads while keeping the user-facing message concise.	codex	\N		[-0.072551,0.009922,0.002934,0.045561,-0.029732,-0.100553,-0.028636,0.030622,-0.03926,-0.051501,-0.021935,0.046006,0.004884,-0.003719,-0.009643,0.003409,0.052946,0.008961,-0.043246,-0.012618,-0.038287,-0.012611,-0.059757,0.105806,-0.093867,-0.068039,-0.081584,0.006155,0.054546,-0.011532,-0.0203,0.024979,-0.031188,0.005793,0.081622,0.151716,0.080505,-0.061958,-0.083965,-0.043919,0.159685,0.000498,-0.061372,0.033809,-0.009705,-0.103758,0.066307,-0.006124,-0.033475,-0.040238,0.007856,0.049287,0.059927,-0.038449,0.007845,0.047837,0.012471,-0.005352,0.017428,-0.00805,-0.011664,0.033917,-0.057239,-0.027651,-0.000493,0.031573,0.073881,-0.062343,0.021462,0.105722,0.037898,0.026761,-0.169976,0.053195,-0.033055,0.073372,0.004116,-0.043204,-0.02423,-0.048557,-0.003229,0.041121,-0.016036,0.048144,-0.008501,-0.05