BUG-31C147A8	bug_31c147a8	Workflow preview reports host workdir instead of authoritative shard workspace	OPEN	P1	P1	The preview payload echoes `repo_root` and `workdir` from spec/input assembly in `runtime/workflow/_admission.py`, but sharded execution resolves `materialized_repo_root` and `materialized_workdir` fr	conversation_review	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 14:59:21.470929-07	\N	2026-04-16 14:59:21.470929-07	2026-04-16 14:59:21.470929-07	ARCHITECTURE	The preview payload echoes `repo_root` and `workdir` from spec/input assembly in `runtime/workflow/_admission.py`, but sharded execution resolves `materialized_repo_root` and `materialized_workdir` from the active fork/worktree binding and enforces workspace-boundary checks in `runtime/workflow/_execution_core.py`. For Docker-sharded workflows, preview can therefore report the wrong code root. Fix by resolving the same workspace authority in preview or by marking workspace as unresolved instead of fabricating host paths.	codex	\N		[0.007692,0.00898,0.02326,-0.042233,-0.006708,-0.084198,-0.088321,-0.073709,0.025192,-0.024871,-0.036841,-0.019115,0.052854,0.034035,-0.023349,-0.017685,0.028237,-0.028387,0.029879,0.004919,-0.016657,0.044048,0.050046,0.030729,0.005763,-0.067049,-0.074364,0.070525,0.004754,0.011638,0.091082,0.04779,-0.026951,-0.055801,0.11989,0.097014,0.042602,-0.016836,-0.028799,-0.00849,0.108883,0.035967,0.033434,-0.051411,-0.040578,-0.017574,0.039974,-0.112974,-0.041818,0.028482,-0.035162,-0.078018,0.064163,0.009567,0.037455,0.067614,-0.033923,0.045484,0.061106,-0.068046,-0.024086,0.020005,0.025968,-0.094512,-0.0355,0.012651,0.038278,-0.021049,-0.027316,-0.030069,-0.005537,-0.004323,-0.074129,-0.065255,0.037708,0.041267,0.012092,-0.029873,-0.001592,-0.109027,0.018621,-0.041635,-0.016729,0.034231,-0.046769,-0.001679,-0.00913,-0.034385,0.140692,-0.040992,0.011761,-0.087427,-0.052129,-0.014804,0.048906,-0.112096,-0.012801,0.093295,0.006685,0.027996,-0.003953,-0.066287,0.042628,-0.014377,0.042101,0.071416,-0.0