BUG-92981B72	bug_92981b72	API server mutates process env from derived WORKFLOW_DATABASE_URL authority	WONT_FIX	P2	P2	The REST entrypoint publishes a derived database URL back into `os.environ` in `_prime_workflow_database_env()` before startup. That makes one fallback-selected authority sticky for the rest of the pr	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 12:36:32.723648-07	2026-04-16 13:40:38.268547-07	2026-04-16 12:36:32.723648-07	2026-04-16 13:40:38.268547-07	ARCHITECTURE	The REST entrypoint publishes a derived database URL back into `os.environ` in `_prime_workflow_database_env()` before startup. That makes one fallback-selected authority sticky for the rest of the process and any child consumers, so later subsystems inherit a mutated env instead of the original explicit authority contract. Evidence: `surfaces/api/server.py:39-45` calls `workflow_database_env()` and then writes `os.environ["WORKFLOW_DATABASE_URL"] = database_url`. Next step: stop mutating process env at startup; pass the resolved authority explicitly to the callers that need it.	codex	\N		[-0.0701,-0.011636,0.008069,-0.046938,-0.021088,-0.141447,-0.05812,-0.000382,0.044935,0.017813,-0.062376,0.046782,0.038485,0.02627,0.011625,0.095197,0.02593,-0.017576,0.001091,0.036233,0.047227,0.068174,-0.024159,0.091408,-0.055242,-0.105864,-0.039674,0.05854,0.036868,-0.027947,-0.020996,0.038227,-0.05798,0.041857,0.051938,0.040043,0.071612,-0.04974,0.033343,0.028398,0.122886,-0.010169,-0.102052,-0.022056,-0.044037,-0.029579,0.041215,-0.062335,-0.121346,0.032367,0.044948,-0.036511,0.014678,0.004727,0.00334,-0.016406,-0.003201,0.05641,0.026738,0.014057,-0.015868,-0.014961,0.015785,0.01087,-0.01249,-0.013913,0.010696,-0.070134,0.034377,-0.095987,0.016632,-0.057918,-0.102804,-0.029353,0.012338,0.005221,0.005753,-0.012011,-0.058023,-0.087833,0.047103,0.030072,-0.051232,0.074194,0.025312,-0.026145,-0.004071,-0.020087,0.100582,0.047788,-0.009621,-0.147292,0.038225,-0.037814,0.089184,-0.014633,-0.018622,-0.069897,0.001511,-0.0