BUG-DCEB232E	bug_dceb232e	Manual bug packets collapse onto a shared fallback fingerprint and lose replay history anchors	FIXED	P2	P2	Root cause: the failure-packet identity path only has strong material when bugs carry receipt-linked provenance or signature tags, but manually filed bugs usually have neither. In live packet output o	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 14:17:31.478222-07	2026-04-16 14:31:37.393575-07	2026-04-16 14:17:31.478222-07	2026-04-16 14:31:48.386834-07	VERIFY	Root cause: the failure-packet identity path only has strong material when bugs carry receipt-linked provenance or signature tags, but manually filed bugs usually have neither. In live packet output on 2026-04-16, BUG-F456562D, BUG-65EC94A3, and BUG-38DF2FF0 are unrelated bugs yet all emitted the same signature fingerprint `ddf076d0cafdcc9799f2`, all reported `historical_fixes.reason_code=bug.historical_fixes.insufficient_signature`, and all reported `provenance_backfill.reason_code=bug.replay_backfill.insufficient_signature`. The runtime evidence matches the code: `BugTracker.failure_packet()` builds signatures from receipt/tag fields plus `source_kind`, and `_build_historical_fixes()` immediately bails out when both `failure_code` and `node_id/job_label` are missing. Impact: bug packets look authoritative but manual bugs are effectively anonymous, so replay backfill, historical fix discovery, and cross-bug clustering silently degrade for the exact class of bugs operators file most often during investigation. Related files: Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_tracker.py, Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_evidence.py. Commands/evidence: praxis workflow tools call praxis_bugs packet for BUG-F456562D, BUG-65EC94A3, BUG-38DF2FF0 on 2026-04-16.	codex	\N		[-0.107611,-0.000601,-0.017836,-0.028158,0.087273,-0.07549,0.000315,-0.009013,-0.108263,-0.005419,0.040263,-0.008733,0.025659,-0.020156,-0.047267,-0.023463,0.034712,-0.036653,0.033164,0.005909,-0.119605,0.062638,0.023123,0.039409,-0.005224,-0.021523,-0.07333