BUG-928B2F35	bug_928b2f35	Workflow preview frontdoors require Postgres despite DB-light preview authority	OPEN	P2	P2	`preview_workflow_execution()` deliberately avoids consulting native default refs so the read-side lane can stay DB-light, but the public CLI and MCP frontdoors still require a Postgres connection bef	conversation_review	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 14:59:21.475032-07	\N	2026-04-16 14:59:21.475032-07	2026-04-16 14:59:21.475032-07	WIRING	`preview_workflow_execution()` deliberately avoids consulting native default refs so the read-side lane can stay DB-light, but the public CLI and MCP frontdoors still require a Postgres connection before calling it. CLI preview goes through `_get_pg_conn()` in `surfaces/cli/workflow_cli.py`, and MCP preview goes through `_load_pg_conn()` in `surfaces/mcp/tools/workflow.py`. That removes the testing lane exactly when the operator is debugging degraded DB conditions. Fix by letting frontdoors invoke preview in a DB-optional mode and only require Postgres when preview asks for DB-backed authority that cannot be satisfied from the spec.	codex	\N		[-0.020646,-0.052396,-0.015066,0.03195,-0.027512,-0.089516,-0.043939,-0.070478,-0.042909,-0.006965,-0.042172,0.04499,-0.011151,-0.070007,0.027777,0.053035,0.129004,-0.045651,0.047848,0.047222,-0.04649,-0.074294,-0.022466,0.040503,-0.075485,-0.122427,-0.052657,0.058507,0.012641,0.020827,0.023107,0.067821,-0.048487,0.037367,0.076287,0.06725,0.094295,-0.054404,-0.042174,-0.026834,0.10036,0.027916,-0.043428,0.026286,0.015473,-0.111601,0.042006,-0.090467,-0.052207,-0.072318,-0.019442,-0.005879,0.013351,-0.051101,0.026997,0.099006,-0.006688,-0.007611,0.052685,0.023355,-0.06031,-0.007701,0.001313,-0.051373,-0.062575,0.031896,0.041206,-0.06113,0.07491,-0.014529,0.01413,0.031256,-0.093092,-0.072102,-0.009125,0.067882,0.024818,-0.064643,-0.002452,-0.126523,0.020587,0.009908,0.023183,0.012289,0.005937,-0.010048,0.020051,-0.069485,0.090957,0.059949,0.039715,-0.020752,-0.063944,0.021578,0.051438,-0