BUG-8CE1A62B	bug_8ce1a62b	praxis_supervisor can select an unresolved launchd database candidate as authority	WONT_FIX	P2	P2	The supervisor discovers `WORKFLOW_DATABASE_URL` from launchd plist env, checks whether the referenced database name exists, and if none of the candidates are proven live it still returns `unresolved_	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 12:36:32.734343-07	2026-04-16 13:40:48.16423-07	2026-04-16 12:36:32.734343-07	2026-04-16 13:40:48.16423-07	RUNTIME	The supervisor discovers `WORKFLOW_DATABASE_URL` from launchd plist env, checks whether the referenced database name exists, and if none of the candidates are proven live it still returns `unresolved_candidates[0]`. That means a stale launchd value can be treated as the active authority even after existence checks fail, which is the opposite of fail-closed behavior and can send the supervisor into the wrong database. Evidence: `runtime/praxis_supervisor.py:223-239`. Next step: make unresolved launchd candidates non-authoritative and require a verified DB target or explicit failure.	codex	\N		[-0.056093,-0.070808,-0.064399,-0.037019,0.031816,-0.038139,-0.053069,-0.035494,-0.099759,-0.002478,-0.001282,0.04337,0.035792,0.027031,-0.011853,0.10579,0.022618,0.018073,0.05299,0.052597,-0.050956,0.058565,0.005976,0.079794,-0.09707,-0.0735,-0.016853,0.000218,-0.02147,0.051259,-0.013833,0.019354,-0.041139,0.009269,0.114654,0.080862,0.058589,-0.037614,-0.095858,0.029074,0.143021,0.016381,-0.100461,0.00288,-0.037348,-0.047746,-0.026803,0.028629,-0.079784,-0.028177,-0.022752,-0.054731,0.074277,-0.028049,0.005575,0.060854,0.079478,0.022963,-0.005566,0.010096,-0.036159,-0.008004,-0.010686,-0.084002,0.00339,-0.01122,-0.056011,-0.098481,0.088334,0.009114,0.031577,-0.027324,-0.098119,-0.040811,-0.044611,0.02954,0.056709,-0.047517,-0.067129,-0.017854,-0.075082,-0.072341,-0.04023,0.014338,0.041403,-0.023771,0.072256,-0.002231,0.111726,0.067335,-0.051405,-0.036011,0.00093,0.010582,-0.010526,-0.002471,0.000423,-0.023841,0.0162