BUG-D3CD86B8	bug_d3cd86b8	Workflow preview omits platform context but claims exact worker-facing payload	OPEN	P1	P1	`preview_workflow_execution()` assembles preview messages through `_execution_model_messages` in `runtime/workflow/_context_building.py`, but real execution adds platform context and sends `full_promp	conversation_review	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 14:59:21.451436-07	\N	2026-04-16 14:59:21.451436-07	2026-04-16 14:59:21.451436-07	ARCHITECTURE	`preview_workflow_execution()` assembles preview messages through `_execution_model_messages` in `runtime/workflow/_context_building.py`, but real execution adds platform context and sends `full_prompt` to the backend in `runtime/workflow/_execution_core.py`. The preview contract and parity test currently prove helper parity, not backend-bound prompt parity, so the lane overstates exactness. Fix by extracting one shared execution-input assembler and having preview either return the final backend-bound prompt or explicitly mark it unresolved.	codex	\N		[-0.017177,-0.038487,-0.005671,-0.01648,0.000218,-0.095249,-0.025191,-0.030633,-0.015355,-0.069456,-0.024938,-0.037713,0.026532,-0.000273,0.061612,-0.008905,0.132189,-0.075875,0.037476,0.013149,-0.041664,0.019247,0.036617,0.06254,-0.003365,-0.043879,-0.052195,0.075705,0.065652,0.029402,0.067206,0.049279,0.005576,0.013704,0.123651,0.107875,0.045798,-0.032696,-0.045029,-0.021749,0.054469,0.032926,-0.041927,0.04456,0.029914,-0.040022,0.064652,-0.068028,-0.060221,-0.045343,0.007438,-0.032405,0.048384,-0.043843,-0.034321,0.076505,-0.024529,0.024086,0.018335,0.007957,-0.121366,0.007067,-0.002111,-0.033119,-0.041828,0.056738,0.019855,-0.058227,0.002235,-0.037843,-0.000859,-0.037309,-0.055386,-0.030997,-0.0064,0.062408,0.040584,-0.063436,-0.078088,-0.11765,0.060246,-0.048592,0.026407,0.055066,-0.010172,-0.021787,0.017461,-0.05477,0.08087,0.020818,0.006785,-0.132881,-0.063281,0.019731,0.077423,-0.013754,0.000779,-0.054663,-0.052619,0.024481,-0.066675,-0.115136,0.140621,0.001447,0.