BUG-AA1B4B54	bug_aa1b4b54	Supervisor treats database-name match as proof of full launchd authority	WONT_FIX	P2	P2	`runtime/praxis_supervisor.py` validates launchd candidates with `_database_exists(database_name_from_url(candidate))`, which checks only whether the database name exists on the local Postgres cluster	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 12:38:07.65938-07	2026-04-16 13:40:43.014452-07	2026-04-16 12:38:07.65938-07	2026-04-16 13:40:43.014452-07	ARCHITECTURE	`runtime/praxis_supervisor.py` validates launchd candidates with `_database_exists(database_name_from_url(candidate))`, which checks only whether the database name exists on the local Postgres cluster. If a launchd plist points at a different host, port, or user but happens to reuse the same database name, the candidate is accepted as authoritative even though the full authority is not verified. Evidence: `_database_exists()` hardcodes `127.0.0.1:5432` and `discover_database_url()` returns the candidate solely on a name match at lines 223-230. Next step: verify the full authority target or cluster identity, not just the database name, before treating a launchd candidate as live.	codex	\N		[-0.042623,-0.072049,-0.048781,-0.045812,0.012098,-0.05375,-0.043919,-0.042863,-0.072776,-0.002422,-0.004845,0.009306,0.035961,0.025649,-0.015996,0.071786,0.06426,0.003164,0.067425,-0.001493,-0.060632,-0.017954,0.024841,0.080305,-0.052246,-0.102833,-0.041233,0.060359,-0.005331,0.038605,-0.002862,0.003146,-0.004322,0.046815,0.111383,0.084274,0.061133,-0.093076,-0.103399,0.001981,0.200535,-0.013718,-0.070505,0.01548,-0.072579,-0.027699,-0.021103,0.053184,-0.080193,-0.04885,-0.021361,-0.035468,0.034568,-0.096955,-0.017554,0.085316,0.033306,0.052151,0.037061,-0.012546,-0.010302,-0.008579,-0.012731,-0.038359,-0.014411,0.002273,-0.018501,-0.075973,0.090171,-0.025126,0.075157,-0.001328,-0.09549,-0.006225,-0.048213,0.051247,0.018295,-0.0092,-0.066351,-0.00739,-0.074861,-0.056117,-0.053647,-0.000809,0.00776,-0.033488,0.032381,-0.0410