BUG-64F981C1	bug_64f981c1	Failure packet helpers swallow backend errors and report empty observability summaries	FIXED	P2	P2	In `Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_tracker.py`, failure-packet assembly depends on `_semantic_neighbor_bundle()`, `_compare_write_sets()`, and `_build_blast_radius()`, but those helpers suppress DB/vec	code_inspection	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:10:18.886959-07	2026-04-16 23:55:30.778547-07	2026-04-16 16:10:18.886959-07	2026-04-16 23:55:30.778547-07	VERIFY	In `Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_tracker.py`, failure-packet assembly depends on `_semantic_neighbor_bundle()`, `_compare_write_sets()`, and `_build_blast_radius()`, but those helpers suppress DB/vector exceptions and return benign empty payloads. `_semantic_neighbor_bundle()` catches vector and tag-search failures with bare `except Exception: pass` at lines 1187-1261. `compare_write_sets()` catches receipt-baseline lookup failures and returns `note: "no comparable successful receipt"` at `bug_evidence.py:482-541`. `build_blast_radius()` catches receipt query failures and returns zero counts at `bug_evidence.py:673-726`. The packet builder then includes `semantic_neighbors`, `write_set_diff`, and `blast_radius` at `bug_tracker.py:1531-1635` without any corresponding error signal. Result: operators can get a packet that looks complete even when the underlying lookup failed, which masks the real blast radius and cluster context.	codex	\N	bug-packet-observability,observability-drift,silent-failure	[-0.026972,0.027835,-0.027709,0.019199,0.009243,-0.073583,-0.048129,0.028721,-0.09859,0.022019,0.049021,-0.040466,0.100655,0.013575,-0.0088,0.025059,0.054058,-0.056553,-0.012914,-0.023201,-0.094696,0.143321,0.061498,0.097903,-0.005469,-0.003155,-0.051618,0.011798,0.051114,-0.045237,0.009136,0.100529,-0.092171,0.025777,0.129986,0.115451,0.025801,0.022566,-0.032563,-0.029524,0.030168,0.021412,-0.060817,0.051615,-0.087549,-0.034892,0.002734,0.014857,-0.01631,-0.116813,-0.024945,0.067728,-0.00634,0.000142,