BUG-46816578	bug_46816578	Semantic neighbor lookup silently falls back to none when vector and tag queries fail	FIXED	P3	P3	`Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_tracker.py:1153-1261` builds semantic neighbors in three stages: pgvector embedding search, text-vector search, then tag-overlap SQL. Each stage is wrapped in bare `exce	code_inspection	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:10:32.016429-07	2026-04-16 22:16:01.560718-07	2026-04-16 16:10:32.016429-07	2026-04-16 22:16:01.560718-07	VERIFY	`Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_tracker.py:1153-1261` builds semantic neighbors in three stages: pgvector embedding search, text-vector search, then tag-overlap SQL. Each stage is wrapped in bare `except Exception: pass`, so any backend error is converted into a quiet `bug.semantic_neighbors.none` or `bug.semantic_neighbors.no_signals` result instead of a surfaced failure. The packet then carries `semantic_neighbors` as if no cluster existed, which makes it look like a bug is isolated even when the neighbor discovery path itself broke.	codex	\N	bug-packet-observability,semantic-neighbors,silent-failure	[0.020904,-0.044016,-0.000984,0.020304,0.072881,-0.077041,-0.093853,-0.069726,-0.094356,0.005922,0.022734,-0.008766,0.009328,-0.04644,-0.052169,0.063225,0.052182,-0.047607,0.025532,-0.011819,-0.115367,0.097716,0.08906,0.023412,-0.018079,-0.007062,-0.041734,-0.09104,0.070133,0.015646,0.029656,0.102478,-0.108366,0.071936,0.086403,0.079526,0.048836,0.015329,-0.096979,0.025262,0.083267,0.073308,-0.06263,-0.029522,-0.02512,-0.020258,-0.057691,-0.004695,-0.02686,-0.096915,-0.028689,0.011687,-0.008549,0.012802,0.035565,0.075121,-0.054159,-0.038542,-0.02398,-0.019638,0.007729,-0.019141,0.0553,-0.06985,0.054046,-0.019532,0.013561,0.004488,0.068731,0.020822,0.065312,0.081635,-0.09748,0.011488,0.010219,0.092091,0.030365,-0.02942,0.031644,-0.070025,-0.102329,-0.059279,-0.029376,0.027332,0.046216,-0.043923,0.006435,-0.041535,0.076011,0.034722,0.022652,-0.032476,-0.009494,0.01019,0.033706,0.005687,0.030311,-0.0