BUG-CE143B50	bug_ce143b50	Write-diff and blast-radius summaries collapse DB failures into empty or zero-state packets	FIXED	P3	P3	`Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_evidence.py:482-541` wraps the baseline receipt lookup in `compare_write_sets()` with `except Exception`, then returns `note: "no comparable successful receipt"` and emp	code_inspection	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:10:43.083142-07	2026-04-16 22:15:17.327851-07	2026-04-16 16:10:43.083142-07	2026-04-16 22:15:17.327851-07	VERIFY	`Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_evidence.py:482-541` wraps the baseline receipt lookup in `compare_write_sets()` with `except Exception`, then returns `note: "no comparable successful receipt"` and empty path sets if the query fails. `Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_evidence.py:673-726` does the same for `build_blast_radius()`, swallowing receipt query failures and returning zero counts. `failure_packet()` wires both summaries into the final packet at `Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/bug_tracker.py:1604-1634`, so a backend failure looks like there was simply nothing to compare or count. That hides both the missing write-diff evidence and the real blast radius of the failure path.	codex	\N	bug-packet-observability,write-diff,blast-radius,silent-failure	[-0.04449,0.043942,-0.058746,0.041352,0.0203,-0.097394,-0.013096,0.069139,0.026113,0.017423,0.050514,0.009766,0.082909,-0.020183,-0.04857,-0.024705,0.003887,-0.082781,0.012458,-0.040737,-0.062183,0.133711,0.050197,0.082695,0.010311,0.014473,-0.048213,0.071518,0.00305,-0.070874,0.033922,0.096666,-0.08057,-0.001678,0.133139,0.02181,0.050996,-0.000347,0.015353,-0.039897,0.056175,0.042397,-0.000868,0.070853,-0.092348,-0.015693,-0.033779,0.034678,-0.029787,-0.079267,-0.002917,0.066515,0.010038,0.035792,0.136534,-0.031464,-0.031371,0.006248,-0.068938,-0.049505,-0.061978,-0.037068,0.003864,-0.039676,0.032356,0.023193,0.031086,-0.005943,0.039394,-0.02505,-0.006569,0.055801,-0.131893,0.067182,-0.026003,0.079254,0.027696,0.011345,-0.090176,-0.022548,-0.078351,