BUG-F2447D6B	bug_f2447d6b	[authority-spiderweb] Provider support is defined by DB registry, runtime adapter registry, and health probes separately	FIXED	P2	P2	Provider capability is split across three different authorities. adapters/provider_registry.py is a compatibility facade over registry.provider_execution_registry, runtime/workflow/runtime_setup.py co	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 21:03:01.751894-07	2026-04-17 02:54:06.392132-07	2026-04-16 21:03:01.751894-07	2026-04-17 02:54:06.392132-07	ARCHITECTURE	Provider capability is split across three different authorities. adapters/provider_registry.py is a compatibility facade over registry.provider_execution_registry, runtime/workflow/runtime_setup.py constructs a separate AdapterRegistry by hand for execution, and surfaces/mcp/tools/health.py derives probe coverage from provider_registry_mod.supports_adapter instead of validating the actual runtime adapter registry. That means supported providers/adapters can look healthy in one surface while the execution path is still wired through a different registry object. This is duplicated responsibility over the same concern, so drift is inevitable and operator checks are not proving the runtime path that actually executes jobs.	codex	\N		[-0.113149,-0.064614,-0.04657,0.028838,0.04233,-0.103139,0.009651,0.011195,-0.065352,-0.067797,0.056792,0.035893,0.014374,0.053718,0.01854,0.076824,0.022884,-0.029111,0.010132,0.075585,-0.074464,0.019965,0.022428,0.095164,-0.117807,-0.080909,-0.029871,0.017093,0.010194,0.00235,0.030083,0.011844,-0.094127,-0.020566,0.051455,0.077737,0.009883,0.001644,-0.077583,0.016447,0.156589,0.016659,-0.013404,-0.002462,-0.017354,-0.050177,-0.00356,0.004843,-0.068846,-0.093981,-0.015588,-0.010732,0.003041,-0.06413,0.003384,0.017388,0.032286,-0.000695,-0.01248,-0.029427,0.022914,0.036383,-0.024829,0.025434,-0.007111,0.024359,0.042375,-0.051298,0.087762,-0.107922,-0.170977,-0.007555,-0.023368,0.028154,0.046793,-0.006493,-0.020322,-0.03109,0.024643,-0.1277