BUG-C03D743F	bug_c03d743f	Workflow DB authority is resolved through duplicated runtime and surface fallback ladders	FIXED	P2	P2	Root cause: workflow surfaces duplicate Postgres authority resolution in `runtime/_workflow_database.py` and `surfaces/_workflow_database.py`, each with process-env, repo .env, and Docker fallback log	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 12:34:35.31632-07	2026-04-16 14:07:55.386373-07	2026-04-16 12:34:35.31632-07	2026-04-16 14:08:46.544806-07	ARCHITECTURE	Root cause: workflow surfaces duplicate Postgres authority resolution in `runtime/_workflow_database.py` and `surfaces/_workflow_database.py`, each with process-env, repo .env, and Docker fallback logic. That means API, MCP, and runtime entrypoints can publish or consume different DSNs for the same repo, and a missing or stale env can be masked by fallback discovery instead of failing at one explicit authority seam. Evidence: `surfaces/api/server.py` primes `WORKFLOW_DATABASE_URL` from `workflow_database_env()`, `_BaseSubsystems.get_pg_conn()` calls `create_pg_conn()`, and both resolver modules independently read `.env` / docker. Next step: collapse resolution to one authority seam and make startup fail closed when the process env does not already supply it.	codex	\N		[-0.085466,-0.06458,0.03109,-0.019025,-0.003459,-0.14423,-0.061562,-0.001987,0.024658,-0.006995,-0.096585,0.035242,0.008754,-0.006595,0.020755,0.025343,-0.013582,0.011345,-0.028164,0.020575,-0.051367,0.018285,-0.050626,0.102103,-0.10258,-0.076625,-0.068215,0.040012,0.00209,-0.004183,0.040975,0.081794,-0.044733,0.071808,0.100773,0.118005,0.043978,0.017486,-0.004275,-0.059282,0.167228,0.011233,-0.032119,-0.049301,-0.013772,-0.042781,0.034493,-0.060362,-0.063001,-0.019228,0.026976,-0.012149,0.040203,-0.017958,0.009759,0.082025,0.009902,0.062815,0.03336,0.034904,-0.040105,0.017352,-0.053352,-0.025638,0.041049,-0.010271,0.067026,-0.058859,0.048294,-0.00447,0.057826,-0.01988,-0.109493,-0.053231,-0.0403,0.005159,-0.010036,-0.040138,-0.071