BUG-79E19DEB	bug_79e19deb	Bug stats undercount replay-blocked work by using global packet-ready totals	FIXED	P2	P2	Observability bug: `BugTracker.stats()` calculates `packet_ready_count` from all bugs with discovered evidence and then derives `replay_blocked_count` as `max(open_count - packet_ready_count, 0)`. Bec	dispatch	\N	\N	\N	automation.deep_hygiene.2026-04-16	\N	2026-04-16 14:08:19.761079-07	2026-04-16 14:15:41.049451-07	2026-04-16 14:08:19.761079-07	2026-04-16 14:15:53.958621-07	VERIFY	Observability bug: `BugTracker.stats()` calculates `packet_ready_count` from all bugs with discovered evidence and then derives `replay_blocked_count` as `max(open_count - packet_ready_count, 0)`. Because packet-ready is not scoped to open bugs, resolved bugs with packets can erase the blocked-open count and make the backlog look healthier than it is. Evidence: `runtime/bug_tracker.py:1910-1968`; an in-process fake connection reproduced `open_count=2`, `packet_ready_count=5`, `replay_blocked_count=0`.	deep_hygiene_automation	\N	bug-stats,observability-drift,replay-blocked	[-0.064453,-0.02417,-0.049948,0.03223,-0.015958,-0.058533,0.002333,-0.006187,-0.039131,0.051767,0.021941,0.036403,0.023945,0.006076,-0.028688,0.00817,0.084805,-0.072369,0.024565,-0.062505,-0.052855,0.072804,0.054278,0.004811,0.036118,-0.049053,-0.098049,0.013353,0.08137,-0.034733,-0.024571,0.062511,-0.033668,-0.03931,0.081463,0.014378,-0.041733,-0.000812,-0.040639,0.078121,0.068883,0.036363,-0.04348,0.012104,-0.038365,-0.026621,0.024275,0.027754,0.024995,-0.007715,0.034637,0.112969,0.001374,0.018992,0.123303,-0.046941,-0.037372,-0.017018,-0.058337,0.068252,-0.056497,0.006341,-0.029219,-0.006901,-0.008406,0.064233,-0.027027,0.038611,0.027775,0.043166,-0.081941,0.066847,-0.038179,0.076157,0.007665,0.000469,-0.06937,-0.016976,-0.03288,-0.063888,-0.004211,-0.116177,-0.013918,-0.026044,0.06357,0.009234,0.034625,0.023155,0.070964,0.004495,0.040636,0.064307,0.022871,0.106542,-0.03131,-0.009892,0.033313,0.050799,-0.0