BUG-D0141011	bug_d0141011	Issue backlog and bug tracker are split across separate read and write authorities	OPEN	P2	P2	The work-intake path is split across `operator_read.query_issue_backlog`, `BugTracker`, and issue-to-bug promotion logic in `operator_write`/`work_item_closeout_repository`. `workflow_query_core` rout	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:14:06.573259-07	\N	2026-04-16 16:14:06.573259-07	2026-04-16 16:14:06.573259-07	ARCHITECTURE	The work-intake path is split across `operator_read.query_issue_backlog`, `BugTracker`, and issue-to-bug promotion logic in `operator_write`/`work_item_closeout_repository`. `workflow_query_core` routes `issue backlog` to the issue read model, but `bug`/`defect` to the bug tracker, while `operator_write` and the closeout repository separately promote and resolve `issues` through `bugs.source_issue_id`. That is two overlapping authorities for the same operational concern. The result is drift: operators can inspect one backlog while automation writes and resolves through another, with the promotion boundary hidden in runtime code instead of a single canonical backlog authority.	codex	\N	authority-split,issue-backlog,bug-tracker	[-0.007775,-0.051836,-0.030717,0.063882,0.036446,-0.057819,-0.003147,-0.003184,-0.036116,0.028439,0.009483,0.019433,0.04838,-0.029837,-0.020872,0.035188,-0.025849,-0.005693,-0.078968,0.006546,-0.015906,0.096348,-0.072597,0.098981,-0.077276,-0.028004,-0.063108,-0.02845,0.021709,-0.045409,-0.032127,0.051634,-0.069551,-0.014515,0.01788,0.033437,0.02295,0.011192,-0.01242,-0.027489,0.077021,0.045466,-0.028908,-0.033537,-0.04558,-0.063023,0.057356,-0.021313,-0.078243,0.015449,-0.050705,-0.043794,0.027719,0.021852,0.028419,0.002861,0.027039,0.038437,-0.040866,0.028769,-0.009574,0.042208,-0.069988,-0.017962,0.098917,-0.08804,-0.007888,0.010424,0.022788,-0.067127,0.005379,0.001747,-0.070635,-0.038408,0.054132,-0.003041,-0.038558,0.049769,-0.030768,-0.113418,-0.009608,0.017489,0.025408,-0.015051,0.059578,-0.0319,0.0