BUG-60F10FF1	bug_60f10ff1	Observability authority split: praxis_status masks missing failure_category_zones while quality_views fails closed	FIXED	P2	P2	Root cause: the status surface and the quality-rollup authority disagree on what to do when failure_category_zones is unavailable. `surfaces/mcp/tools/operator.py` wraps the zone lookup in `try/except	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 20:52:32.235055-07	2026-04-16 22:18:35.647181-07	2026-04-16 20:52:32.235055-07	2026-04-16 22:18:35.647181-07	ARCHITECTURE	Root cause: the status surface and the quality-rollup authority disagree on what to do when failure_category_zones is unavailable. `surfaces/mcp/tools/operator.py` wraps the zone lookup in `try/except` and silently falls back to empty zone counts, then still reports a clean adjusted_pass_rate. `runtime/quality_views.py` treats the same authority as mandatory and raises `RuntimeError` when no zone map can be loaded. That split means one operator-facing surface can look healthy while the DB-backed quality materializer refuses to run, so the system has two incompatible truths for the same failure-category authority.	codex	\N		[-0.017137,-0.064296,-0.033497,-0.000385,0.039631,-0.139164,-0.062895,0.021069,-0.103674,0.026424,0.069146,-0.031765,0.056309,-0.022573,0.025525,0.055336,0.028883,-0.067203,-0.028957,0.058772,0.007911,0.060919,-0.025104,0.009412,-0.077613,0.024686,-0.033021,0.030321,0.103843,-0.041931,0.039812,0.045413,-0.027774,-0.023675,0.110987,0.087958,-0.050852,-0.083111,-0.101928,-0.011167,0.024927,0.034332,-0.03071,-0.00738,-0.008371,-0.034553,0.022768,-0.018388,0.002466,-0.113815,0.010336,0.00938,0.012246,0.011111,-0.016785,0.047918,-0.051037,-0.022113,-0.040126,0.015588,-0.016181,0.067534,0.002538,-0.026354,0.087064,0.054292,0.007575,-0.029893,-0.015787,0.060701,-0.081626,0.009191,-0.057413,0.026891,0.048496,0.044181,0.010555,-0.090535,-0.025214,-0.095833,-0.053109,-0.042824,-0.067564,-0.01142,0.02424,-0.084293,-0.017447,-0.011601,0.06075,0.01308,0.08841,0.0