BUG-47281CFB	bug_47281cfb	praxis_status undercounts workflows and hides high-volume failures by hard-capping receipt sampling at 5000	FIXED	P2	P2	Concrete manifestation: `surfaces/mcp/tools/operator.py` builds `praxis_status` from `list_receipts(limit=5000, since_hours=...)`, so the status surface never inspects more than the first 5000 receipt	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 20:52:41.872435-07	2026-04-16 22:22:07.095109-07	2026-04-16 20:52:41.872435-07	2026-04-16 22:22:07.095109-07	VERIFY	Concrete manifestation: `surfaces/mcp/tools/operator.py` builds `praxis_status` from `list_receipts(limit=5000, since_hours=...)`, so the status surface never inspects more than the first 5000 receipts in the time window. That means pass_rate, adjusted_pass_rate, failure_code counts, and the implied total_workflows can silently undercount once the system crosses the sample cap. Combined with the broad failure_category_zones swallow, the command can report a neat-looking summary while missing the very load spike or failure burst operators need to see.	codex	\N		[-0.054347,-0.004105,-0.026869,0.039034,0.037614,-0.140564,-0.010949,0.069253,-0.03438,0.002262,0.003862,-0.013144,0.048742,-0.0366,-0.010468,-0.030203,0.021723,-0.042652,0.018662,-0.068825,0.047318,0.069804,0.007484,0.056007,-0.030874,-0.003561,-0.044833,0.018883,0.047922,-0.015801,-0.005487,0.055403,0.040126,-0.005724,0.141591,0.05102,-0.037545,-0.05896,-0.029138,-0.039681,0.055019,0.034714,-0.021482,0.023933,-0.035108,-0.023818,0.00654,-0.037665,-0.021169,-0.001386,0.055828,0.041766,0.090005,0.007375,-0.038854,-0.031072,-0.00037,-0.113109,-0.048534,-0.031279,-0.084883,-0.015172,-0.020403,-0.048611,0.012977,0.064369,0.018339,0.039267,0.030525,0.095509,-0.054113,0.038465,-0.089704,0.026799,0.02406,-0.018004,0.005355,-0.081339,-0.086066,-0.09515,-0.065601,-0.000561,-0.035072,-0.018198,0.021522,-0.031389,0.034559,0.061863,0.051244,-0.061246,0.035775,0.042418,-0.043917,0.098285,-0.008161,0.053349,-0.025374,-0.00749,0.000713,-0.