BUG-02B39B8D	bug_02b39b8d	[authority-spiderweb] Workflow database authority is resolved in three places with different fallback behavior	FIXED	P1	P1	Workflow DB authority is not owned by one resolver. Runtime code uses Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/_workflow_database.py, surface helpers wrap that in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/_workflow_database.py, an	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 21:02:56.559227-07	2026-04-16 22:50:29.809354-07	2026-04-16 21:02:56.559227-07	2026-04-16 22:50:29.809354-07	ARCHITECTURE	Workflow DB authority is not owned by one resolver. Runtime code uses Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/_workflow_database.py, surface helpers wrap that in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/_workflow_database.py, and the supervisor has its own discover_database_url path in Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/praxis_supervisor.py. Those paths do not behave identically: the runtime resolver can pull from process env, repo .env, and docker-compose; the supervisor adds launchd plist probing before falling back; surface helpers merely wrap the runtime resolver. The repo itself currently ships a .env file without WORKFLOW_DATABASE_URL, so the documented workflow frontdoor fails unless the caller injects the variable externally. That is split authority plus inconsistent fallback, not a single explicit contract.	codex	\N		[-0.096783,-0.057655,-0.00589,0.0045,-0.006063,-0.087977,-0.049505,0.013196,-0.031567,-0.015469,-0.049462,0.033536,0.030255,0.038012,-0.000224,0.083646,0.019616,0.002805,-0.011854,0.04086,-0.040506,0.029693,-0.018483,0.05549,-0.127907,-0.066075,-0.092154,0.007898,-0.026272,0.019312,-0.003079,0.069206,-0.01291,0.003568,0.047343,0.089869,0.079551,0.029176,-0.04911,0.009896,0.117972,0.054207,-0.010809,-0.036263,-0.043527,-0.040892,0.039058,-0.038096,-0.106453,-0.059533,0.02176,-0.046063,0.006356,0.043062,-0.001505,0.067438,0.026324,0.025867,0.021706,0.002737,0.053386,-0.000533,-0.02556,-0.054505,0.069597,-0.076782,0.013011,-0.072425,0.034887,-0.067387,0.004558,-0.047817,-0.087446,-0.062251,