BUG-FC3201F5	bug_fc3201f5	[authority-spiderweb] Workflow CLI frontdoor still runs two routers and delegates between modern and legacy entrypoints	FIXED	P1	P1	The modern CLI frontdoor in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/cli/main.py and the legacy workflow CLI in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/cli/workflow_cli.py both stay live and call into each other via compatibili	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 21:02:51.512188-07	2026-04-16 22:50:30.349062-07	2026-04-16 21:02:51.512188-07	2026-04-16 22:50:30.349062-07	ARCHITECTURE	The modern CLI frontdoor in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/cli/main.py and the legacy workflow CLI in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/cli/workflow_cli.py both stay live and call into each other via compatibility shims. main.py routes `generate`, `validate`, and `stream` back to workflow_cli.main(), while workflow_cli.py delegates route/help/tool discovery back to surfaces.cli.main. That means there is no single authoritative router, and the same command behavior can drift or recurse across two entrypoints instead of one. This is the kind of split authority that keeps producing stale imports and broken aliases.	codex	\N		[-0.075687,-0.101081,-0.0033,-0.061589,0.054381,-0.135051,-0.100261,-0.030877,-0.036427,-0.08205,-0.028434,0.034265,-0.002525,0.025357,0.061004,0.089932,-0.038843,-0.038858,-0.004229,0.023023,-0.004707,0.026808,-0.029312,0.030613,-0.100031,-0.065208,-0.068252,-0.010843,0.030019,-0.033628,-0.007715,0.124907,-0.086086,-0.016917,0.032468,0.076264,0.038936,0.005434,0.046577,-0.000472,0.123505,0.069076,-0.025119,-0.065795,-0.083549,-0.078993,0.017475,-0.030055,-0.054804,-0.067698,0.019659,-0.066347,-0.0377,0.000703,0.038871,0.024632,-0.022374,-0.001975,0.044052,-0.021515,-0.018385,0.056095,-0.001689,-0.014619,-0.004431,-0.092226,0.040719,-0.045213,0.06605,-0.056055,-0.03389,-0.008429,-0.117258,0.017818,0.070231,-0.018072,-0.004696,0.047065,-0.035733,-0.157742,0.008177,0.011853,0.020598,0.050564,0.101208,-0.052094,-0.035766,-0.047524,0.105038,0.048548,0.023182,-0