BUG-5D88A809	bug_5d88a809	Health-side queue gate is orphaned: QueueAdmissionGate exists but dispatch never consults it	FIXED	P2	P2	runtime/health.py exposes QueueAdmissionGate and queue_admission_check as if they were a dispatch-facing admission surface, but the actual submission path in runtime/workflow/_admission.py continues t	manual	\N	\N	\N	cluster.queue_admission_authority.2026-04-16	\N	2026-04-16 20:59:50.123042-07	2026-04-16 23:08:22.717045-07	2026-04-16 20:59:50.123042-07	2026-04-16 23:08:22.717045-07	WIRING	runtime/health.py exposes QueueAdmissionGate and queue_admission_check as if they were a dispatch-facing admission surface, but the actual submission path in runtime/workflow/_admission.py continues to call its own _enforce_queue_admission() helper. There is no wiring from the queue gate in health.py into the submit path, and the public helper is not used anywhere in the runtime code. That leaves the new gate as a parallel utility, not an authority. It matters because operators can reasonably assume the health gate is the same admission rule dispatch uses, but the code currently tells two different stories. Evidence: runtime/health.py:686-759 defines QueueAdmissionGate and queue_admission_check; repository-wide search shows no runtime caller for queue_admission_check or QueueAdmissionGate outside health.py itself; runtime/workflow/_admission.py:147-154 and runtime/workflow/_admission.py:1169 enforce admission independently. Suggested next step: wire the runtime submission path to call the shared gate or remove the dead health-side admission helper entirely and keep the health module strictly observational.	codex	\N	cluster:queue-admission,dead-adapter,wiring,health	[-0.059789,0.015479,-0.062759,-0.016145,-0.013026,-0.106817,0.002137,-0.037298,0.00915,0.006549,0.004798,0.034753,-0.017338,-0.000109,0.048888,-0.037484,0.077085,-0.106416,-0.055636,-0.034346,0.017389,0.028723,0.031962,0.055389,-0.129643,-0.125692,-0.087427,0.00521,0.046256,0.015991,-0.016045