BUG-586B5664	bug_586b5664	workflow recall renderer hides backend failures behind a clean no-results message	FIXED	P2	P2	workflow_query_core.handle_recall() returns status=unavailable plus error_type/error_message when the knowledge graph search fails, but surfaces/cli/mcp_tools.render_recall_payload() only checks wheth	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:16:20.08026-07	2026-04-16 21:54:51.671494-07	2026-04-16 16:16:20.08026-07	2026-04-16 21:54:51.671494-07	VERIFY	workflow_query_core.handle_recall() returns status=unavailable plus error_type/error_message when the knowledge graph search fails, but surfaces/cli/mcp_tools.render_recall_payload() only checks whether results is empty. That means a backend outage is rendered as "no results found" instead of an unavailable/error state, so operators cannot tell the difference between a true empty search and a broken recall authority. Relevant files: surfaces/api/handlers/workflow_query_core.py:868-886 and surfaces/cli/mcp_tools.py:65-79.	codex	\N		[-0.032129,0.004057,0.022694,0.080673,0.027852,-0.039315,-0.049732,0.007427,-0.002313,-0.05153,0.024307,-0.009593,0.063214,-0.034289,0.002952,-0.002438,0.038886,-0.079899,0.044284,-0.049266,0.040613,0.112156,0.048438,0.066008,-0.061966,-0.04551,-0.059491,-0.048102,0.022248,0.02671,0.00265,0.052598,-0.080061,0.048458,0.146955,0.091014,-0.044404,-0.002042,-0.023257,-0.082321,0.021369,0.087722,-0.051993,0.026283,-0.018365,-0.040708,0.030719,-0.081089,-0.019968,-0.047698,-0.005213,0.064552,0.002086,-0.016913,0.05111,0.057686,-0.044617,-0.018978,-0.106877,-0.032654,-0.012851,-0.131289,-0.017218,-0.109822,-0.040627,0.00101,0.03054,-0.113254,0.09197,-0.024473,0.040252,-0.003935,-0.10528,-0.041861,0.022256,0.128638,0.012964,-0.049924,-0.061583,-0.030247,-0.018118,-0.034379,-0.055583,0.081879,0.048468,-0.034658,-0.039209,-0.066839,0.127384,-0.014111,-0.012046,-0.042328,-0.03357,-0.009112,0.028907,-0.021313,0.089561,0.039873,-0.055071,-0.001909,0.045648,0.00801,0.048174,-0.016192,0.039651,0.0