BUG-DF15A751	bug_df15a751	Replay-ready bug view mutates bug provenance on GET by default	FIXED	P2	P2	The replay-ready bug read path is not read-only. `surfaces/api/handlers/workflow_query_core.py:1278-1316` runs `bt.bulk_backfill_replay_provenance(open_only=True, receipt_limit=1)` whenever `refresh_b	code_inspection	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:17:51.613171-07	2026-04-16 22:36:19.846052-07	2026-04-16 16:17:51.613171-07	2026-04-16 22:36:19.846052-07	WIRING	The replay-ready bug read path is not read-only. `surfaces/api/handlers/workflow_query_core.py:1278-1316` runs `bt.bulk_backfill_replay_provenance(open_only=True, receipt_limit=1)` whenever `refresh_backfill` is true, and `surfaces/api/rest.py:2389-2391` exposes that behavior through GET `/api/bugs/replay-ready`. The unit test `Code&DBs/Workflow/tests/unit/test_workflow_query_handlers.py:4352-4440` asserts the maintenance backfill payload as part of the happy path, so the hidden write is being codified instead of isolated. Impact: simply inspecting replay-ready bugs can mutate provenance and make the result depend on background maintenance instead of a stable read contract.	codex	\N		[-0.104755,-0.046394,-0.031017,0.083025,0.015977,-0.048901,0.011798,0.018618,-0.010282,0.04024,-0.004284,0.028799,0.019714,-0.033782,-0.048002,0.013434,0.053709,-0.050498,-0.018323,-0.014518,-0.029354,0.105144,0.032807,0.077193,-0.054338,-0.042901,-0.099976,-0.018181,0.028155,-0.07031,-0.031033,0.090776,-0.082676,-0.031224,0.110597,0.109802,0.000681,-0.038707,-0.044157,0.02414,0.055886,0.004582,-0.055553,-0.003958,0.007149,-0.049657,0.069605,-0.003427,-0.019548,0.001865,0.010159,0.049959,-0.005683,0.025549,0.01424,-0.016029,0.050341,0.019079,-0.058515,0.030194,0.013065,-0.023727,0.048621,-0.041143,0.011442,0.044755,-0.003292,0.001045,0.059032,-0.070558,0.042021,0.048518,-0.082748,-0.030343,0.037488,0.080789,-0.026985,-0.050452,-0.054871,-0.117405,-0.040122,-0.08668,0.002439,-0.008585,0.047551,-0.022685,0.047842,0.050266,0.072263,0.000771