BUG-B3100333	bug_b3100333	Moon build state is assembled from multiple authorities instead of one canonical workflow moment	OPEN	P2	P2	Moon cannot honestly present or generate one authoritative workflow state because the build surface reconstructs its payload from several authorities instead of one canonical moment object. The compil	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 23:13:01.991539-07	\N	2026-04-16 23:13:01.991539-07	2026-04-16 23:13:01.991539-07	ARCHITECTURE	Moon cannot honestly present or generate one authoritative workflow state because the build surface reconstructs its payload from several authorities instead of one canonical moment object. The compiler explicitly stops at bootstrap planning state and requires later review/hardening before execution authority exists, while the build payload is reassembled from definition, build bundle, review state, candidate manifest, reviewable plan, compiled spec, and execution manifest. This split makes auto-creating a working Moon flow unreliable and forces the UI to render a stitched snapshot instead of one durable source of truth.	codex	\N		[-0.058957,0.002801,0.086052,-0.005015,0.051283,-0.106222,-0.087249,-0.064143,-0.013472,0.019747,-0.034857,-0.033084,0.004979,-0.054621,-0.005719,0.010123,-0.035664,-0.013959,-0.030526,0.013105,0.024409,-0.060459,-0.043066,0.075417,0.053827,0.063189,-0.03963,0.021145,0.090723,-0.063149,0.009049,0.057133,-0.050732,-0.018397,5.5e-05,0.103903,-0.006184,-0.039711,-0.059798,-0.067517,-0.02316,-0.022538,-0.043242,0.001325,0.006617,0.043837,0.04023,-0.07782,-0.048935,-0.028765,-0.027169,-0.03962,0.012484,0.010996,0.020549,-0.015972,-0.021955,-0.002353,0.042074,-0.003132,-0.056077,0.09365,-0.044444,-0.017812,0.150118,0.069381,-0.039157,-0.118067,0.008553,-0.051129,0.012401,-0.067685,-0.047666,-0.004824,-0.012632,0.036142,-0.018399,0.042144,-0.007957,-0.063617,-0.013478,0.006512,-0.01936,0.039237,0.020355,-0.0278,0.038626,0.063454,0.122503,0.048529,-0.01772,-0.065018,0.068305,0.044256,0.025611,0.