BUG-AE645514	bug_ae645514	Workflow CLI command authority is duplicated between legacy and modern frontdoors	FIXED	P2	P2	The workflow command surface is split between the legacy `surfaces.cli.workflow_cli` entrypoint and the newer `surfaces.cli.main` / `surfaces.cli.commands.workflow` frontdoor. The two paths do not sha	manual	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:14:22.255976-07	2026-04-17 03:09:44.214718-07	2026-04-16 16:14:22.255976-07	2026-04-17 03:09:44.214718-07	ARCHITECTURE	The workflow command surface is split between the legacy `surfaces.cli.workflow_cli` entrypoint and the newer `surfaces.cli.main` / `surfaces.cli.commands.workflow` frontdoor. The two paths do not share a single authoritative command registry: `workflow_cli.py` still carries its own command/help/index logic, while `main.py` imports the modern handlers and registers `dry-run` even though the handler is missing. This is a classic split-authority failure mode: command availability, help text, and runtime wiring can drift independently, and one broken import takes down the modern surface before the fallback path can even be reasoned about.	codex	\N	split-authority,cli-frontdoor,workflow-cli	[-0.043823,-0.086644,0.024567,-0.014037,0.060312,-0.099067,-0.073184,0.004969,-0.015161,-0.068308,-0.018403,0.009565,-0.01016,0.04981,0.084914,0.031734,-0.031365,-0.044806,-0.038338,0.043083,-0.056781,0.068573,-0.003714,0.012516,-0.125987,-0.063377,-0.092332,-0.007031,-0.001133,-0.010131,-0.043108,0.113279,0.009045,-0.016067,0.048432,0.108527,0.045005,0.031748,0.058469,-0.031555,0.121321,0.081056,0.000425,-0.053434,-0.039548,-0.031627,0.030103,-0.072642,-0.031533,0.008295,0.021415,0.006649,0.04543,-0.001287,0.039878,0.066933,-0.025218,0.034487,0.06139,0.017798,-0.05275,0.063315,-0.030378,-0.019971,0.02822,-0.086417,0.035384,-0.077631,0.044063,-0.028175,-0.051235,-0.008017,-0.105994,-0.005233,0.035561,0.027064,-0.013024,0.021423,-0.08971,-0.167942,0.020042,0.01938,0.001249,0.036955,0.034871,0.004603,-0.056551,-0.065843,