BUG-8AA3A6DA	bug_8aa3a6da	Operator packet inspection silently downgrades missing authority to derived or missing	FIXED	P2	P2	`NativeOperatorQueryFrontdoor._fetch_workflow_run_packet_inspections()` in `surfaces/api/_operator_repository.py` swallows broad exceptions when importing `runtime.execution_packet_authority` and when	code_inspection	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:17:51.644439-07	2026-04-17 03:17:15.694318-07	2026-04-16 16:17:51.644439-07	2026-04-17 03:17:15.694318-07	VERIFY	`NativeOperatorQueryFrontdoor._fetch_workflow_run_packet_inspections()` in `surfaces/api/_operator_repository.py` swallows broad exceptions when importing `runtime.execution_packet_authority` and when deriving inspections from packets. If the materialized row path or the derived packet path fails, the code keeps going and labels the record `missing` or `derived` instead of surfacing a hard failure. That means the observability layer can look healthy enough to render even when the packet-inspection authority itself is broken, so contract drift is hidden behind a lower-fidelity source marker.	codex	\N	packet-inspection,observability-drift,silent-failure,source-demotion	\N	{"evidence": ["Code inspection: _fetch_workflow_run_packet_inspections() catches import and derivation exceptions, then records packet_inspection_source as missing/derived.", "The returned observability summary counts materialized/derived/missing sources, so a broken path can still be rendered as a lower-quality but apparently valid packet view."], "bug_class": "observability_drift", "hypothesis": "Packet inspection should fail closed or expose an explicit error source instead of demoting the row to derived/missing.", "next_steps": ["Make packet inspection source demotion explicit and queryable as an error state.", "Add a regression test that forces the helper import/derivation path to fail and asserts the failure is surfaced, not hidden."], "cluster_key": "packet-inspection-source-demotion", "related_files": ["Code&DBs/Workflo