BUG-029FE124	bug_029fe124	Workflow dry-run has two implementations, so tests cover a different executor than the live CLI/API dry-run path	FIXED	P2	P2	Live dry-run entrypoints in the API, CLI, and MCP tool all call runtime.workflow.dry_run.dry_run_workflow(), but the integration test suite exercises WorkflowRunner.run_workflow(dry_run=True) instead.	code_inspection	\N	\N	\N		\N	2026-04-16 16:28:26.360877-07	2026-04-17 03:21:52.089708-07	2026-04-16 16:28:26.360877-07	2026-04-17 03:21:52.089708-07	TEST	Live dry-run entrypoints in the API, CLI, and MCP tool all call runtime.workflow.dry_run.dry_run_workflow(), but the integration test suite exercises WorkflowRunner.run_workflow(dry_run=True) instead. Those paths are not the same authority: the runner carries its own receipt-writing, verification, and blocked-job handling, while the runtime dry-run used by operators is a separate module. That leaves room for the test harness to pass while the live dry-run contract drifts. Evidence: Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/api/handlers/workflow_run.py lines 135-148, Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/cli/workflow_cli.py lines 291-300, Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/mcp/tools/workflow.py lines 1441-1459, Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/workflow/dry_run.py lines 47-133, and Code&DBs/Workflow/tests/integration/test_workflow_runner.py lines 271-295.	codex	\N		[-0.083073,-0.02248,0.020052,0.050633,0.055004,-0.131851,-0.098589,-0.042985,0.004341,-0.072624,-0.002864,-0.014153,0.002998,0.015598,0.040042,-0.06263,0.05848,0.039865,-0.037054,0.030254,0.001058,0.026735,0.005956,0.058304,-0.083201,-0.049527,-0.005317,-0.013097,-0.03482,-0.011435,-0.011172,0.007883,-0.036851,0.008776,0.034835,0.050375,0.048989,0.021333,-0.011866,0.040016,0.105732,-0.036005,0.040302,-0.051035,0.025839,-0.064049,-0.034139,-0.019303,-0.098304,0.0673,0.052369,-0.007765,0.099951,0.006264,-0.019009,0.030414,0.060536,0.047803,0.003093,0.053868,-0.034326,-0.007947,0.005504,-0.024767,-0.052051,-0.026167,-0.010705,-0.048228,0.08198,-0.074687,